# Git Workflow

## Branch Policy

**NEVER commit directly to `master`.** All work happens on feature branches.

### Branch Naming

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Article | `article/{slug}` | `article/playwright-visual-testing` |
| Feature | `feat/{short-description}` | `feat/add-search-filters` |
| Bug fix | `fix/{short-description}` | `fix/broken-og-image` |
| Design/UI | `style/{short-description}` | `style/card-hover-effects` |
| Docs | `docs/{short-description}` | `docs/update-readme` |
| Refactor | `refactor/{short-description}` | `refactor/layout-components` |
| CI/CD | `ci/{short-description}` | `ci/optimize-docker-build` |

Use lowercase, hyphens as separators. Keep branch names short (2-4 words).

### Before Starting Work

1. Check current branch: `git branch --show-current`
2. If on `master` â€” create and switch to a new branch before making changes
3. Pull latest master first: `git pull origin master`
4. Create branch: `git checkout -b {type}/{description}`

## Conventional Commits

All commit messages follow the [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/) specification.

### Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

### Types

| Type | When to use |
|---|---|
| `feat` | New feature or new article |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `style` | CSS, design, formatting (no logic change) |
| `refactor` | Code restructuring (no feature/fix) |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `test` | Adding or updating tests |
| `ci` | CI/CD pipeline changes (deploy.yml, Docker) |
| `chore` | Maintenance, dependency updates, config |
| `content` | Article content edits (not new articles) |

### Scopes (optional)

| Scope | Applies to |
|---|---|
| `article` | Blog article content |
| `ui` | Frontend components |
| `layout` | Astro layouts |
| `seo` | Meta tags, schema.org, sitemap |
| `config` | Project configuration |
| `deps` | Dependencies |
| `docker` | Docker/deploy infrastructure |
| `skill` | Cursor skills |

### Examples

```
feat(article): add Playwright visual testing guide
fix(ui): card image overflow on mobile
style(layout): update footer spacing and colors
docs: update pipeline documentation
refactor(ui): extract ArticleCard into separate component
ci(docker): optimize multi-stage build
chore(deps): update astro to 5.4.2
content(article): fix typos in OWASP article
feat(skill): add conventional-commits skill
```

### Rules

- Description starts with lowercase verb (add, fix, update, remove, refactor)
- Max 72 characters for the first line
- No period at the end of the description
- Body explains **why**, not **what** (the diff shows what)
- Use `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer when introducing breaking changes
